title: Welcome to the next meetup of R-Ladies Chennai!
description:
Interested in R? Join us to learn & discuss R with a fun and supportive group! Come and join us at our R- Ladies Chennai Meetup for a fun evening of networking and learning R. We welcome all R-users of all experience levels alike. Bring your R-friends & family too.

What you need to do before the meetup:

We are going to be working through the FREE edX course Foundations of Data Analysis - Part 1: Statistics Using R. Please sign up for this course at https://www.edx.org/course/foundations-data-analysis-part-1-utaustinx-ut-7-11x-0 .
If you are a newcomer here or new to R, don't worry- we will get you up to speed !

Bring your laptops to code along with us, if possible!

title: Welcome to the first meetup of R-Ladies in Chennai!
description:
Welcome to the first meetup of R-Ladies in Chennai! Learn R with us!

We will have a short introduction to R and the Rladies group. Then, we will work on a sample dataset and learn some very useful R functions that will enable you to analyze the dataset and visualize it.

Please bring your laptops to code along with us, if possible!

Bring your friends along too!

Schedule:

• 4:00pm-4:30 pm: Networking

• 4:30pm-4:45 pm: Introduction to Rladies

• 4:45pm-6:00 pm: Introduction to R with sample datasets

title: Welcome to a virtual meetup of R-Ladies Chennai!
description:
Interested in R? Join us to learn & discuss R with a fun and supportive group! Come and join us at our R- Ladies Chennai Virtual Meetup for a fun event of networking and learning R. Newbies are welcome too!

Main agenda of this session :

To teach you how to do data analysis on a dataset

What you will learn during this session :

Importing data with the readr, data.table and readxl packages
Data cleaning process using the "tidyr"(pivot_longer and pivot_wider functions) and "dplyr " packages
Importing and cleaning an example dataset and analyzing it

title: "Unsupervised Learning with K-means Clustering"  with Praveena Mathews
description:
Come and join us at our R- Ladies Chennai virtual meetup for a fun event of networking and learning R. Newbies are welcome too! During this meetup of R-Ladies Chennai, we are excited to go through “Unsupervised Learning with K-means Clustering”.

Session title: Unsupervised Learning with K-means Clustering

About the workshop: This workshop will introduce “Unsupervised Learning with K-means Clustering” . You will learn what unsupervised learning is and how to find subgroups (i.e., structure) within a larger group of unlabeled data using k-means clustering.

The Zoom link will be emailed to those who have registered for the meetup closer to the event. In case there is a problem with attending on Zoom, please log in on https://meet.google.com/gwz-zxkc-rtr and email chennai@ladies.org immediately.

title: Creating an R Package: Why and How?
description:
Hello ,

Come and join us at our meetup “Creating an R Package: Why and How?” on Friday, January 6th from 6 - 8 PM to hear Dr. Heather Turner speak. This is a hybrid event.

The event will be held at the IIT-Madras Research Park (Hall 1, Block E) at Tharamani, Chennai. Please find the map at
https://goo.gl/maps/VpAeyWQTsdtYmv6B7

Zoom Meeting ID: 222 101 2022
Passcode: 2022

Dr. Heather Turner is a leader in the R and RSE communities, internationally recognized for contributions towards improving equality, diversity and inclusion (EDI). She is an established Research Software Engineer (RSE) in the field of Statistics, specializing in the R programming language. See more: https://warwick.ac.uk/fac/sci/statistics/staff/academic-research/turner/

We are part of R-Ladies, a worldwide organization that promotes diversity in the R community via meetups and mentorship in a friendly and safe environment. There are over 120 R-Ladies chapters around the world, and we are excited to be part of one here in Chennai.

title: A Tutorial On Linear Regression
description:
Join us at our R- Ladies Chennai virtual meetup for a fun event of networking and learning R. Newbies are welcome too! During this meetup, we are excited to help you learn linear regression.

About the session: In this session, we will analyze a dataset using linear regression to explore the relationship between a response variable and explanatory variables which may be categorical or numerical. We will also quantify the fit of models and learn about outliers, leverage and influence.
